tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/utlaloc00.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Tlaloc00</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/anim_1.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(4/3/02 9:03:04 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousethebackroomsecretsspoilers.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=10585.topic>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Fear pathing changes?</span><hr size=1> Can anyone confirm a rumor that the pathing of the hill mobs in Fear has changed over the past couple months, making a break much harder? <br>We had a horible time with a fear break last night and wondered if it was just a bad night or in fact the pathing was changed and caught us off guard.<br>Little embarassing getting smacked down so hard breaking Fear, the way we have done a hundred times easily heheh<br><br>Thanks in advance.<br><br>Tlaloc<br> <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/ujibooyemcarini.showPublicProfile?language=EN>JibooYemCarini</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(4/3/02 11:10:26 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousethebackroomsecretsspoilers.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=10585.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Fear pathing changes?</span><hr size=1> just AE it <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/ucalyxto.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Calyxto</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(4/3/02 11:49:55 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousethebackroomsecretsspoilers.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=10585.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Fear pathing changes?</span><hr size=1> I don't recall downloading any new files for fear so I'd have to say it hasn't changed. Makes sense right? <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/utrezl.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Trezl</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(4/3/02 12:12:11 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousethebackroomsecretsspoilers.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=10585.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Fear pathing changes?</span><hr size=1> hill pathing has always been a little goofy.<br><br>I've noticed no changes in the break.  Probably just had a bit of bad luck.<br><br> <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/ufayenae.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Fayenae</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(4/3/02 12:51:02 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousethebackroomsecretsspoilers.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=10585.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Fear pathing changes?</span><hr size=1> i concur with Jimboo...AE it. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/udatalore.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Datalore </A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(4/3/02 2:01:08 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousethebackroomsecretsspoilers.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=10585.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Fear pathing changes?</span><hr size=1> We send in a warrior with SOE first, he makes one turn around the hill and takes off due East. Groups zone in and go west, when all are in zone warrior gets COH to camp, clearing his aggro because of the large distance. We then kill whatever comes into camp, and start pulls. Still get about 6-8 mobs in camp every time, though, so bring two good chanters. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/uflatin.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Flatin</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/anim_1.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(4/3/02 3:40:02 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousethebackroomsecretsspoilers.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=10585.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Fear pathing changes?</span><hr size=1> Pathing changes are not required to download new zone file. Only time you download zone files if loal characters were added, or there's a major change in a zone's objects <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/ugazgul.showPublicProfile?language=EN>gazgul</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(4/5/02 12:40:04 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousethebackroomsecretsspoilers.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=10585.topic&index=7>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Fear pathing changes?</span><hr size=1> There are new mobs in fear such as the ones that drain mana and the aligators.  A glare lord now paths through the top of the ring of fire so people camping out there have a chance to gain agro. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon3.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/upercifulpellinore.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Perciful Pellinore</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/white_fire.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(4/5/02 10:22:22 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousethebackroomsecretsspoilers.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=10585.topic&index=8>Reply</a>    <br>Community Supporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Fear pathing changes?</span><hr size=1> We have reports that some of the Gorrilas see invis.  Haven't confirmed but you may want your FD scouts to verify. <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/upercifulpellinore.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Perciful Pellinore</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/white_fire.gif" BORDER=0> at: 4/5/02 10:23:20 am<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/uqalarrubican.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Qalar Rubican</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(4/5/02 11:31:20 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousethebackroomsecretsspoilers.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=10585.topic&index=9>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Fear pathing changes?</span><hr size=1> Having someone go in to fear before the rest of the group is a BAD idea if you're learning how to break it.  Once that person dies, the mobs will path around the portal in a huge group and since they have such large agro radius', your raid will be flattened, I guarentee.<br><br>Just take 2 groups of people who don't lose their cool, and 2 good enchanters and keep them healed = win.<br><br><br>*acts cool*<br><br>JUST AE IT LAMO <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START 8) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/glasses.gif ALT="8)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br><br> <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/ulaguer.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Laguer</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(4/5/02 7:42:08 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousethebackroomsecretsspoilers.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=10585.topic&index=10>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Fear pathing changes?</span><hr size=1> Hardest thing I've noticed in Fear lately is that the Scarelings numbers have increased.  Their agro range is huge and they cause most of the trains that come to get you if you use the west wall camp. <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table><table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top"> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousethebackroomsecretsspoilers.showPrevMessage?topicID=10585.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousethebackroomsecretsspoilers.showNextMessage?topicID=10585.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br><a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousethebackroomsecretsspoilers.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=10585.topic&index=10><img src=http: